Senator:  I would love to get coverage through the exchange.  My husband and I are self-employed.  We’re attorneys and have our own practice.  We make a nice living, but we’re not wealthy, certainly not by Northern Virginia standards.  When the ACA was enacted it was a godsend.  Our premiums for our family of 5 (all of us have preexisting conditions) were manageable.  We qualified for no subsidy, and it was expensive but it was do-able.  This year we had the best policy we’d had since being self-employed.  $1600 monthly premium, but we could swing it.  For 2018, that policy isn’t offered.  Most similar policy has a $3200 per month premium.  What are we supposed to do? As a practice of two with no employees, we don’t qualify for group insurance.  My eldest son has a seizure disorder, I have severe asthma.  My youngest has kidney issues.  But we simply cannot afford $36,000 annually for medical insurance.  Trump and his people have put my family in a horrendous, dangerous position.  What are we supposed to do?
